[phase-4] DONE

Summary:

**Built**: `ridgeline ui [build-name] [--port <n>]` — a fully offline, dark-mode localhost dashboard served from Node's built-in `http` module on `127.0.0.1` with default port 4411. Three routes (`GET /`, `GET /state`, `GET /events`), three SSE event types (`state`, `budget`, `trajectory`) with monotonic ids, 200-per-type replay buffer, `Last-Event-ID` replay support, 20 s heartbeats, and 2 s polling fallback on SSE drop.

**Design tokens**: All palette/typography/spacing tokens per `constraints.md` are CSS custom properties on `:root`. Hex values appear only inside `:root` and favicon SVG strings (enforced by test). Exactly three `@keyframes`. `prefers-reduced-motion` replaces the running-pill pulse with a static 2 px info-cyan border. Inline SVG favicon updates color on state change without reload.

**Contrast helper**: `src/ui/contrast.ts` exports `brightenForContrast(accent, bg, target=4.5)` using the HSL-stepper algorithm from the spec. Every accent/fill pair is verified `≥4.5:1` at build time and baked into the served CSS.

**Tests**: 14 new test files, 112 new passing tests covering smoke, SSE replay, file-watch byte-offset tracking, design tokens, reduced-motion, offline guarantee, a11y structure, contrast, and CLI preflight wiring.

**Deviations**: (1) Criterion 44's `≥16:1` is the design doc's approximation — actual computed ratio is 15.52 (still deep AAA). (2) Criterion 45 axe-core/pa11y substituted with hand-asserted structural checks (jsdom/pa11y can't be installed under sandbox). (3) Pre-existing 28 greywall git failures persist. (4) `lint:agents` unavailable under sandbox.
